==English==
===Noun===
'''dihydrogen'''
#{{chemistry}} the [[divalent]] [[radical]] formed from two separate [[hydrogen]] [[atom]]s or [[ion]]s
====Usage notes====
*Used informally in [[dihydrogen monoxide]], the supposed scientific name for water
*Used in mixed salts, such as [[calcium dihydrogen phiosphate]]
===Adjective===
'''dihydrogen'''
#{{chemistry}} describing a [[dihydrogen bond]]